defaultQuestion 1: Are crimes being recorded by the police when they should be? Are crimes being categorised correctly?default&#xa0;
defaultWe have all seen the 
defaultcontinued 
defaultreductions in recorded cr
defaultime over the last several years and the ‘gap’ between recorded crime statistics and the crime survey results.  This ‘gap’ is arguably one of the reasons behind some of the dissatisfaction we hear 
defaultfrom the public 
defaultabout published crime statistics.
default&#xa0;
defaultLocally, 
defaultthis ‘gap’ has been relatively small and consistent over the years due to the ethical approach adopted
default locally, following the National Crime Recording Standard (NCRS) 
defaultto the letter
default.
default&#xa0;
defaultWhat has 
defaultnot
default happened over this period is a 
defaultproper and informed 
defaultdebate 
defaultabout the victi
defaultms ‘needs’ and a more common-
defaultsense approach to recording for certain crime categories.  For example, there is a tendency to 
default‘
defaultcrime
